# For tenant schema
To create a new migration file
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/tenant_migrations/alembic.ini revision -m"<<JIRA-CARD-NO>>_<<Readable-Description>>"`

To run migrations
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/tenant_migrations/alembic.ini upgrade head`

To merge migrations on a diverged multiple head scenario
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/tenant_migrations/alembic.ini merge <<revison1>> <<revision2>>`

To look at the history
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/tenant_migrations/alembic.ini history`

# For Common schema
To create a new migration file
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/common_migrations/alembic.ini revision -m"<<JIRA-CARD-NO>>_<<Readable-Description>>"`

To run migrations
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/common_migrations/alembic.ini upgrade head`

To merge migrations on a diverged multiple head scenario
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/common_migrations/alembic.ini merge <<revison1>> <<revision2>>`

To look at the history for common schema
    `poetry run alembic -c ./src/migrations/common_migrations/alembic.ini history`


Further informations also exists in the ADR
https://mckinsey.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/OVX9/pages/1002307738/TechCME+Database+Migration+Tool+Selection+-+Orp+GenAI
